rComments: She's a great storyteller which makes the class so much more enjoyable.
Had the pleasure of taking her fourth-year seminar on Greek laughter. She's great, take-home midterm and exam with three simplistic presentations based on an article she gave you.

Amazing prof! She made Greek myth so interesting and always shared her unique viewpoints on the myths. The class was also super easy, as long as you make an effort to actually show up and study/read instructions for the paper. I highly recommend this prof, this class was so chill!

Kostala is AMAZING! Take this class if you need an elective! Incredible story teller and keeps you engaged throughout the lectures. It would be better if she asked for some audience participation, as only she does the talking. Super interesting content. 2 midterms, 1 paper and a final. Do not hesitate to take Greek myth with this prof!

I love her lectures! I think she is a very talented story teller. She clearly loves teaching Greek myth. I think what I love most is that she shows the impact that Greek myth has on current things like movies or sayings. She often shows cute little comics and video clips that are always a welcome change of pace in the lecture.

This prof's a gem! Great bird course BUT only take it if you think you'd be genuinely interested in greek culture/stories... She IS a great storyteller and the midterms are so straightforward! Just go to class, type all you can and you're set! Assignment is long but she's very flexible in terms of what you can do. Must take elective at Uottawa!

An awkward lecturer who often trails off or mumbles parts of her sentences. She clearly knows and loves the material but she's so uncharismatic that it muddles her explanations. Her powerpoints are also vague and poorly worded.  I'd recommend using her lectures as the starting point and google for more context and clarity.
An amazing prof. Very interesting and easy enough class if you put in a little bit of effort. 100% recommend.

Clearly enjoys teaching the material, so much background in the field to be taken away from this solid prof. Mid-term, medium-sized paper, take-home final. Great course, great prof. Wish they could all be like this.
Great class, very detailed lectures. Very minimal slides are posted, therefore attendance is mandatory. She really knows her stuff and gives a detailed lecture every time. Midterms are easy!

She is so nice and is always happy to be teaching Greek Myth. She knows the material super well and she teaches very clearly. Her tests and assignment were super easy and straightforward. She is very generous with marks as well.

Overall good prof! I find Greek mythology interesting so it was easy to pay attention in class. Material can be overwhelming, there's a LOT to memorize for tests. If you go to class and take notes, just study those, you won't even need the textbook. If not, the textbook can fill in the blanks. Easy to talk to and very nice prof!

Professor Kostala is the bomb. She gives amazing lectures, and some of the most fair exams I have written in university. The textbook is very optional (lots of Greek Myth info can be found online) and she is always willing to help or make things more clear. I wish I could take this class again! Go to every class, study her reviews and get an A+ !
She gives an outline of the midterm, and study guide right before the midterms. If you follow them it is an easy A. Content is very interesting too.

She's the best! Write down everything she says, if something doesn't make sense, go see her. I didn't even use study guide, just memorized all the slides & notes & got A+. Had two midterms + 1 assignment & final. Midterms can be long. For our semester, all tests had short or long questions, no MCQs. Never used textbook. Super sweet & enthusiastic

She is an absolutely phenomenal prof! I barely went to the lectures but she posted the slides and you have the textbook to catch up with! Take detailed notes if you can, sometimes remember who is who can be confusing! She gave us a list of deities names to help us with the spelling! She's super cute and very nice. I would definitely take it again

Loved this professor! She makes the information easy to understand and goes over it really well in class so if you pay attention there really is no way you can get a bad mark on the exams. She gives out detailed exam outlines so you are well prepared for them and is very clear in her assignment criteria. She's really sweet!

Very sweet and caring professor.  Goes out of her way to make sure you get a good grade. Lets you know in detail whats on the midterms and final. As long as you attend class and take good notes its almost impossible to get a bad mark.

The class has been completely overhauled since last year. The test no longer have a multiple choice component and instead are completely based upon regurgitation of word-for-word myths that are vaguely taught in class. You are required to read about them and make your own study notes from the book as the slides are useless.

If you do the assigned reading, go to class, and take notes, you'll easily ace. HOWEVER, her lectures and slides are ALL OVER the place. If you don't have the book to read to relate it to the lecture, then the course will be way harder than it should. I did this mistake before the first midterm and learned from it.

As long as you take notes, pay attention in class and study, you will ace this course! This course is so interesting, because of the Greek mythology stories and discussions about Homer &more. Prof shows video clips of pop culture connected with Greek myth and she shows comics! She is also very friendly! The assignments, midterm and final are easy!

AMAZING !!! Really enjoyed her class this semester, her study guide was basically the exam. Go to class, ATTENDANCE IS A MUST, take some notes, and youll be more than fine. Also has a decent sense of humour and makes lectures stimulating and interesting!! 1010 would take her again.

I really enjoyed professor Kostala lectures. There are lectures to do but I thought the book was really good and complimented what we covered in class. Her lectures quickly became my favorite to attend as she is interesting, is really good at conveying the essentials of the myths and shows a lot of clips. She's super sweet & I loved her course!

Professor Kostala, although very sweet, is very disorganized in her lectures and a bit scatterbrained. Her midterm was way too long for such a short amount of time and a few questions were ridiculous but overall it was fairly easy. The content is really interesting but requires a lot of precise memorization. Following her study guide is a MUST.

She is a dynamic and interesting woman who DEMANDS actively participating students. If you don't like group projects and presentations of playspoetryetc you will NOT like this class (participation is worth 20% people). But if you can stand that, she posts detailed notes of every class online and it is quite enjoyable. You learn a lot.
Lectures are all over the place, but she gives you a lot of resources to succeed. DEFINITELY recommend this course if you're looking for something new/ to lighten your load.
Amazing Prof for an amazing class!! Class is super easy. Midterms and final are all multiple choice and the group assignment was fun to work on.
Fantastic prof!

Class was a joke as far as grading goes. She would literally give you the answers to the test and ALMOST encouraged cheating. Did learn a lot, and it was interesting but there were too many movies. She encouraged creative assignments which was refreshing.

I loved her. She was quirky and fun and approached early Greek history from a very engaging and broad perspective. I highly recommend her for anyone who is looking for a good introduction into Greek history. She designed the course to be relatively easy while still teaching us a great deal.
great prof and great class!!

Best prof for the best class ever. It's basically story time. Really interesting how she relates Greek myths to each other and to the bible. I would recommended to anyone! Gives very very very clear test reviews - study those and you'll ace the exams!

She is seriously one of the best profs ever with one of the coolest class you could ever take. Efharis Kostala is so nice, funny and knowledgable. Her class is easy enough and it is very interesting. I wish I could take it again!
Very nice, but insanely boring. She is, however, one of the easiest professors you will ever have. Very detailed exam reviews and slide shows. You can never go to class and still get a 90.

Took her class as part of the only 2 electives we have in Engineering. It was a Godsend.Basically, she works hard to make you get the best grade you can(A+);yet I can't understand how some people still manage to do bad on her exams. Do not hesitate, she's a good easy prof, the subject is very interesting; you really have nothing to lose.

Great myth class. Highly recommend it. Recently changed the format of the class FOR THE BETTER. Less creative assignments and more multiple tests. She prepared you well for the tests with her awesome study guides. No excuse to do worse than 80%. She's very good with technology so expect a lot of great things from her.

I was expecting Heather Loube to teach this but Kostala did a fine job. I had a lot of fun learning the alphabet and culture. She's a little weak with military stuff but amazing with the mythology since she teaches the myth course. There were some good movies/documentaries shown in class. Tests were good bc she gave out study guides beforehand!
Great prof! The class is very interesting, and her assignments are easy and cover the course material. Definitely a top class!

She posts study guides for each midterm, if you use that guide as a checklist you are sure to do well. The essay expectations are very clear. She gives you all the content you need, you just need to put it into a thesis and channel in some creativity. Great course. Best one in University I've taken!
She seems very nice and most of her lectures are rather interesting. Her class is ridiculously easy. The exam was all multiple choice and she provided study questions well ahead of time.
Great Prof! Her lectures are great and she gives you everything you need in order to get a good mark- so long as you put in a little effort. A really fun and very interesting class!
She's nice, and helpful; however, she rambles on and on...

I had her for Greek mythology on saturday mornings and went to every class, hungover or not. She was so fun and obviously was passionate about the subject. She was always clear and stayed within the text without reading from it. She also asked for a lot of participation from the class but it was all voluntary. It was a very comfortable class. A+

....EASY... class was on satuday ... so i never went. Just read the textbook and slides.. 2 essays which were easy, yet had no written comments on them indicating where to improve. Multiple choice midterms worth 10% each that had 60-80 questions.. Take Home exam was EASY... Lots of work but EASY EASY EASY EASY EASY.

NOT HARD TO UNDERSTAND AT ALL!! My favorite prof to date. She gives you EVERYTHING you need to get a great mark in this class. Midterms are fair, amazing reviews are given for them, basically outlining what will be on them. Essay's are marked pretty easy, final was a breeze. Responds to e-mails and requests for help SO promptly answered. AMAZING.
Very difficult to understand. I'm sure she knows what she's talking about, but the slides don't allow for much note taking or understandability.

Does not edit her slides or her exams, and it seems as if she uses a translator or something... things don't make sense, and often lead to confusion...things that could change your grade. She is inconsistent, and doesnt follow a very logical form of anything... is all over the place. Exams cover irrelavent material and are not that easy.
Anyone hating on her because of her accent is rude. She tries so hard and she is an awsome prof. She knows her stuff really well and she does awsome slides and its very appealing.
I found this class very interesting and learned quite alot. She is a good proof, quite clear and helpful, and the assignments and tests are not too shabby either.
This class was well organized.  She handed out study sheets which told us exactly what to expect on the exam which were very helpful for studying.

She is a great prof very knowledgable and very interested I really enjoyed going to her classes she really makes things interesting.  She does have an accent so you have to listen carefully! But she is very helpful and a very easy marker.  I would take as many classes with her as possible. The only thing she needs to change is not allowing people t
I love kostala

Her essay was a breeze, tests were a breeze, but the content was fascinating.  Her natural enthusiasm made the class really interesting.  She needs to shut up her students that keep chating during lecture.(Most likely those who are complaining about the "super-long essay.")
Excellent course; very flexible in terms of assignments, and it's obvious that she is very interested herself in terms of the subject matter. And she marks VERY easily.

Greek tragedy - this class was a tragedy.  She was so disorganized and changed her mind all the time.  Poor teaching and poor management of time. Too bad, because it could have been a great course with a different professor.

Nice person, but not a great prof.  Her expectations for tests were unclear and she seemed to change our syllabus daily so we never knew what plays to read.  We harldy ever got more than a half way through a play before moving on.

if you follow the text its a great class, but be prepared to have to pick apart what she says with questions to amke sure that you understand her VERY thick accent. Long, HARD essay assingment. Midterm is easy.

I absolutely LOVED this class. Greek Myth was by far my favourite. I didn't mind her accent at all, it actually made the class even more interesting. She definitely knows her stuff! I'm taking another one of her classes this semester!

Greek Mythology was an interesting course.  Sadly, most of what I learned was done reading the text. Once you get past the accent... never mind,  you don't even have to go to class.  Just get the syllabus.

Greek Mythology was said to be interesting. But with her accent, you can't understand a thing! And her final assignment is a CRAZY huge essay. If you like hard work, then feel free to take the class. I recommend the class, but maybe not the prof.
